Key Match Events: Breel Embolo scored off a low cross in the 75th minute.
Bukayo Saka scored a stunner from outside the box five minutes later.
England scored all of their spot-kicks to beat Switzerland 5-3 in penalties.
Trent Alexander Arnold buried the winning spot-kick.
Pre-Game Insights: No pre-game insights provided in the article.
Post-Match Reflections: Bukayo Saka said it was one of his best nights for England and that he felt they dominated the whole game.
Bukayo Saka expressed feeling for Switzerland and redemption after missing a penalty in the Euro 2020 final.
Boris Becker congratulated England and commended their penalty shooting.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match went to extra time and penalties due to the scores being level at 1-1.
Harry Kane was substituted after a tussle with Xhaka.
Switzerland made multiple substitutions in extra time.
